Class TicTacToe

java.lang.Object
TicTacToe
public class TicTacToe extends Object
The TicTacToe class represents a game. The game includes the user's score, the bot's score, the TicTacToe table, every index on the TicTacToe table, the symbol that is used both by the bot and the user, and the number of repeats of the game.

    • calcSpot

      public void calcSpot(String spot, String symbol)
      calcSpot method is used to calculate the user's/bot's move on the table. Sets one of the indexes of the table to user's/bot's symbol based on the user's/bot's inputted spot number. Reprints the table everytime the method is called.
      Parameters:
      spot - represents what spot of the table is being used
      symbol - represents the symbol that the user/bot uses

    • userPlay

      public void userPlay(String spot, String symbol)
      userPlay method will calculate their move given the user's input. This method calls the calcSpot method.
      Parameters:
      spot - represents the user's inputted spot they wish to play in
      symbol - represents the user's symbol

    • botPlay

      public void botPlay()
      botPlay method will randomize the bot's move and picks a spot that is not occupied. This method calls the calcSpot method.

    • checkWin

      public boolean checkWin()
      checkWin method checks every winning possibility in the TicTacToe game. Adds to the user's/bot's score after every win.
      Returns:
      returns true when as soon as there's an available win or if all indexes of the game are filled: resulting in a tie. Returns false otherwise.
